text: Hi y'all...question for anyone familiar with forms, is there any known issue why an embedded HS form wouldn't show up if it's inside an inline thank you message form module of a HS website page?

I would think because the thank you message gets added via javascript.

If you’re using hubl, that hubl likely wont be evaluated.

If you’re using javascript. I would think it would result in an error.
I’ve worked around this in the past by making the inline thank you display a button to reveal the content I wanted to show in the current page.

thanks, we had talked about using a button as an option as well and tried to see if the embed code would work alone...and it didn't
_womp womp_
yea the trick i had to do was have a function declared in my js, then have a button in the thank you message that had an onClick=“functionname”

feedback I’ve had before - it would be nice if when publishing an update to a module/template/file if we could provide an optional comment to note what the change was, then in the revisions that comment would show next to the revision.

It’s a simple but easy solution to the problem of looking through file revisions going “idk what the heck changed”

This would ALSO make the fact revisions doesn’t have a diffing mechanism a little less of a big deal
